         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">[…] ¶  ¶ 120 specimens, in fruit as well as in flower, is a large number. — I have no idea what a fair remuneration would be. ¶  ¶ I notice amongst Mr Gulliver's plants the enclosed plant ( ¶ Antennar...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">73.00.00b</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From Samuel Hannaford</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RB MSS M1, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">[…]<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">An unknown amount of text missing.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>120 specimens, in fruit as well as in flower, is a large number. — I have no idea what a fair remuneration would be.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     </seg>MEL has <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>many specimens collected by T. A. Gulliver in the Central Highlands and West Coast of Tasmania in 1873; <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>it is probable that M asked Hannaford to suggest a fair payment for this collection, and it is on this basis that the item is dated to 1873. It cannot be dated to earlier than October 1871, when news reached Australia that M had been appointed a Baron.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I notice amongst Mr Gulliver's plants the enclosed plant (<seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">
                     <name key="Antennaria">Antennaria</name>
                  </hi>
               </seg> sp.) I find it commonly here (H. Town)<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Hobart Town, where Hannaford lived for several years.</p>
               </note> by road sides, sides of ditches &amp;c, <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>much in the same situtations as we see <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Gnaphalium</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">luteo album</hi>
               </seg>. I never found it in "cultivated ground" as Mr Gulliver has done.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Wishing you well through all your troubles and anxieties, I am, as ever</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">My dear Baron</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Yours most sincerely</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Sam Hannaford</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">The Baron Von Mueller</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>&amp;c<space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>&amp;c.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
